wikipedia_page.main: Carlotte Mae Wubben-Moy (born 11 January 1999) is an English footballer who plays as a defender for Arsenal in the FA Women's Super League. She previously played college soccer for the North Carolina Tar Heels in the United States and has represented England at multiple youth levels from under-15 up to under-21. Wubben-Moy received her first England Women's Senior camp call up in September 2020. She made her debut for the England Women’s team in March 2021.
